Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.52,0:00:03.19,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}In the moment, the truth is suddenly revealed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.61,0:00:04.65,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Once it starts rolling, it won't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.33,0:00:06.69,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There is a big surprise today. Those two will appear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.05,0:00:08.56,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}There will be danger on the platform.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.08,0:00:10.33,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Seeing through the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.65,0:00:12.16,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A child with the intelligence of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.63,0:00:14.77,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.29,0:01:41.57,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}We were going to Hokkaido by the\Nnew Northern Star number 3 train.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.77,0:01:44.13,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}While it was going through the Seikan tunnel...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.65,0:01:46.68,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The jewelry trader, Izumo Keitaro{\rHonorifics - Narration Off\be10}-san{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.20,0:01:48.97,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Was shot to death from behind his head.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.07,0:01:53.15,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The criminal then opened the window\Nof the room and jumped off the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.60,0:01:57.62,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Later, in the tunnel, the suspect was found...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.36,0:02:00.29,Narration Off,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The body of Asama Yasuji...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.68,0:02:03.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This case...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.41,0:02:06.96,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the unpublished work by my father are identical...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.88,0:02:12.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Reveal your identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.16,0:02:15.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're already suspected,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.76,0:02:17.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Auntie.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.56,0:02:24.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The North Star #3 Express Leaving Ueno (Part 2).
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.59,0:02:37.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.14,0:02:40.95,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Kudo Yukiko\NShinichi's mother
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.18,0:02:40.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, you're so bright.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.57,0:02:44.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't matter if you were a stranger,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.76,0:02:48.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you can't fool your own son by just altering\Nyour hair style and lipstick color.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.93,0:02:52.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It took me a while to set this hairstyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.61,0:02:58.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's your reason for disguising yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.04,0:03:01.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, why can't I disguise myself?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.70,0:03:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Japan, I'm so famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.62,0:03:06.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How many years ago are you talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.81,0:03:07.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.95,0:03:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I got on this train because...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.62,0:03:13.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I read some news in a Japanese newspaper\Nwhile I was in Los Angeles.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.63,0:03:17.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The robber who tried to rob a jewelry shop said some weird things,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.92,0:03:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then ran away without taking anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:22.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, it's really...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.55,0:03:25.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, according to Yusaku...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.26,0:03:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The professional robbers inexpertly planned the crime...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.11,0:03:32.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what the robber said when he was running away,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.93,0:03:35.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It's not supposed to be like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.75,0:03:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's identical to the work he wrote ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.21,0:03:44.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although there is a difference from the novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.56,0:03:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the place robbed was an antique\Nstore rather than a jewelry store.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.15,0:03:50.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What happened next?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.18,0:03:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We called the jewelry store.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.41,0:03:59.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We asked if the owner planned to take\Na long distance journey by train.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.09,0:04:02.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the owner of the antique store in the novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.12,0:04:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gets killed in the train tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.24,0:04:09.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then they said he will get on the Northern Star six days later.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.31,0:04:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you stop them?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.08,0:04:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H... How was I supposed to know it would\Nhappen while I went to the bathroom?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.08,0:04:20.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At least, you should have discussed it with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.10,0:04:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} was with Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} all this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.01,0:04:27.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, you should have done something to prevent the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.14,0:04:32.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Then, you think his death was my fault?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.73,0:04:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't say that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.33,0:04:41.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the writer of the novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.32,0:04:45.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He took the earlier Northern Star and should be at Sapporo by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.65,0:04:48.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we called the jewelry store,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.21,0:04:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They didn't tell us which one of the three trains he will take.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.85,0:04:54.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, Yusaku and I took different trains.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.98,0:05:00.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He got on Train 1 while I got on Train 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.88,0:05:04.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other one, Train 5 crossed the tunnel early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.37,0:05:05.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So we believed that one would be safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.77,0:05:10.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So this trick is better to do at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.36,0:05:13.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what's the trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.81,0:05:13.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.38,0:05:16.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you ask Dad about the story?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.46,0:05:18.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.91,0:05:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What! He forgot the trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.19,0:05:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because it was a work written ten years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.85,0:05:35.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said when the novel was stolen, only\Nthe first part of the story was finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.33,0:05:37.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was stolen?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.00,0:05:41.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, a person from the publishing firm that kept the draft,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.76,0:05:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was robbed while stopping at a bank.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.45,0:05:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, would that robber be the...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.78,0:05:51.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.82,0:05:53.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were three robbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.54,0:05:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The head was called... Asama Yasuji,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.34,0:05:59.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one found dead in the tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.99,0:06:02.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't it strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.18,0:06:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come the robber who stole the novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.84,0:06:08.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has been murdered as written in the novel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.33,0:06:10.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.79,0:06:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.14,0:06:14.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.60,0:06:16.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:19.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah... I'm with this Auntie...!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.52,0:06:26.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were talking with me, onee{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.78,0:06:29.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.98,0:06:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's go to the lobby car.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.95,0:06:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad said he's going to show off his deduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.12,0:06:39.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like he beat you to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.25,0:06:41.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be good if he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.06,0:06:49.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Deduction show? Isn't the criminal the body found in the tunnel,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.42,0:06:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asama Yasuji?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.39,0:06:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the criminal is Asama Yasuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.88,0:06:59.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what's your deduction about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.49,0:07:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about his intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.57,0:07:01.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Intentions?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.56,0:07:05.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the key to unfolding this puzzle is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:09.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Asama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} broke into Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s jewelry store, he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.33,0:07:12.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It's not supposed to be like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.15,0:07:15.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this was the case, then it would have been a difficult puzzle.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.86,0:07:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if Asama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were partners,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.50,0:07:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then everything can be explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.38,0:07:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.47,0:07:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} allowed his store to be robbed on purpose,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.64,0:07:31.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then have that jewelry returned back to him afterwards, secretly,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.18,0:07:37.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But also take the insurance money for the\Nstolen jewelry. He found Asama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.65,0:07:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he would get 50% of the insurance money.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.52,0:07:42.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when the robbery happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.13,0:07:46.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} pressed the alarm button\Nto force Asama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.30,0:07:51.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the very beginning, Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't intend\Nto allow the robbers to get the jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.73,0:07:52.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.56,0:07:55.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He intended to show off that he got the robbers well,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.32,0:08:00.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he could boost his popularity for the\Nnext election to increase his votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.32,0:08:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, Asama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} ran away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} became worried and received a call from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.92,0:08:13.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get on the specified Northern Star Train,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.15,0:08:16.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And finish the transaction, away from the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.06,0:08:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was called, out this way,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.98,0:08:24.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was shot by Asama, and Asama, who\Nwanted to escape from the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.15,0:08:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hit his head hard on the ground, and died.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.54,0:08:35.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that I think about it, the bass decided to\Ncatch the Northern Star after the robbery.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.68,0:08:38.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, he sudden y decided to catch the train instead of the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.33,0:08:43.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how did Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} first get to know Asama?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.86,0:08:45.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's probably "that".
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't it on the newspaper before?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.13,0:08:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Izumo{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was dealing drugs in the black market.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.26,0:08:54.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was proven not to be true.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.86,0:08:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's like what the detective said,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.51,0:09:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wasn't dealing with legal trading business.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.01,0:09:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This kind of disgusting person shouldn't be the next mayor.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.91,0:09:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How dare you say that in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.41,0:09:10.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.81,0:09:12.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.11,0:09:15.40,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If it was an ordinary incident... Uncle's\Ndeduction would be accurate...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.19,0:09:20.47,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}But this incident is the same as the draft written by my Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.03,0:09:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.48,0:09:28.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't that robber belong to the "Three-people gang"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.75,0:09:29.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.85,0:09:31.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know the names of them all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.09,0:09:36.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, only the head Asama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and the dead woman are known,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.14,0:09:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But we don't know who the third member is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.65,0:09:43.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, in the last robbery at the jewelry\Nstore, only Asama was involved.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.77,0:09:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess the other one retired from the gang.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.86,0:09:54.46,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It's possible that one of these four people\Nbelong to the "Three-People Group".
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.03,0:09:58.52,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That means, someone here has read my Dad's novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.19,0:10:01.44,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is the room plan for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.74,0:10:06.02,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If there's a way to not be discovered when\Nmoving into another bedroom, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.74,0:10:11.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hang on, how about using some type of equipment?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.07,0:10:15.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Azusa{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} has a practice gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.51,0:10:18.90,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Kaetsu{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} brought some fishing equipment.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.31,0:10:22.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Aoba{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} brought a bamboo sword and equipment for kendo.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.81,0:10:25.64,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Ishizuchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} has some golf clubs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.45,0:10:30.63,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Right, if the body of Asama{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was\Nthrown away from the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.21,0:10:33.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Before Izumo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was killed... Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.70,0:10:38.35,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If that thing was used, then he would be able to fool us easily...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.66,0:10:39.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Nishimura.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.17,0:10:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We just received a phone call from the site,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.62,0:10:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The time which Asama fell from the train has been determined.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.10,0:10:53.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the speed of the train and the position\Nof the body, it occurred at about 4:10 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.04,0:10:58.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It matches with the time when the criminal\Nentered the room, as witnesses say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.20,0:11:00.67,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}How can it be!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.60,0:11:05.20,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then the criminal threw away the body in a relatively short time,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.83,0:11:07.29,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And vanished from the room?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.40,0:11:09.16,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.84,0:11:11.77,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}It can't be done by a human being.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.02,0:11:15.00,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Then, how did he do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.99,0:11:16.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.14,0:11:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, the broken pieces from the window are still missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.20,0:11:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tell them to search for it carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.92,0:11:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, the belt on the dead body has some strange stuff stuck on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.12,0:11:30.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some strange stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.37,0:11:34.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, something like plastic tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.84,0:11:40.66,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Wait. If that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.70,0:11:42.12,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Over there...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.14,0:11:46.34,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}If it's really there...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.42,0:11:50.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Found it. I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.18,0:11:52.43,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The criminal used this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.21,0:11:55.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The criminal should be that person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.61,0:12:00.73,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}That person murdered Izumo{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} and diverted\Nour attention onto Asama{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.13,0:12:06.61,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}By using the construction of the Northern Star and Seikan tunnels.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.60,0:12:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.72,0:12:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured everything out now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.97,0:12:14.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.01,0:12:18.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really a crappy method that Dad used in the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.43,0:12:24.29,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}A kid wearing black-frame glasses smiled arrogantly\Nbecause he was confident of his win...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.74,0:12:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.68,0:12:28.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.40,0:12:33.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we can make fun of him for being the loser this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.73,0:12:34.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.72,0:12:36.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom, in that novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.17,0:12:39.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was there anything about a young guy with black-frame glasses?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.24,0:12:43.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, a boy who loves deductions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.41,0:12:45.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember, he's too confident of himself,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.98,0:12:47.49,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}On top of his amazing deduction,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.96,0:12:51.77,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He didn't realize his life will pay for the truth he discovered...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.96,0:12:55.83,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}... That doesn't sound good...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.66,0:13:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, don't think too much, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.47,0:13:09.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although the incident is identical to Yusaku's novel,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.01,0:13:12.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} won't be killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.77,0:13:15.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The boy in the novel doesn't have any evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.90,0:13:19.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he sets a trap and ends up falling into his own trap.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.87,0:13:21.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's way different from Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.63,0:13:27.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think will be murdered, but the situation is almost the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.51,0:13:31.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have no evidence so far.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.59,0:13:37.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know the trick used, and the person who did it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.96,0:13:41.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I don't have any evidence to prove that he's the one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.13,0:13:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then we can't catch him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.25,0:13:49.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess the evidence is still inside his luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.62,0:13:53.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But with this situation with everyone\Nthinking Asama Yasuji is the one,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.12,0:13:56.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It is impossible to ask him to show his luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.30,0:13:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.80,0:14:00.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.74,0:14:03.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's follow the storyline of the novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.48,0:14:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.53,0:14:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While you were in the front of Asama's\Nroom, you saw something weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.76,0:14:10.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.27,0:14:15.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it happened just before the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.70,0:14:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right before we entered the Seikan tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.03,0:14:24.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In front of Asama's room, there was a very strange, very long...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.03,0:14:25.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Long,"... What was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.32,0:14:29.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.72,0:14:31.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.65,0:14:36.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't worry, I will remember it very soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.43,0:14:40.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right? That someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.86,0:14:47.30,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Satsu Horo Station
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.64,0:14:46.83,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Sapporo, Sapporo.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.34,0:14:49.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.42,0:14:51.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I will take a walk within a short distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.35,0:14:53.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You have to follow me closely.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.18,0:14:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, if he gets close to you, I will shoot\Nhim with the anesthetic needle.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.82,0:15:00.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's so exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:01.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.21,0:15:03.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.76,0:15:06.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See you. I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.35,0:15:11.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here, Conan?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.48,0:15:15.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, let's go. Natsue{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and others should be waiting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.13,0:15:21.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ahh, I think I forgot something on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.23,0:15:24.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll ask to see if I can go and have a look,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.42,0:15:25.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can go back first.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.29,0:15:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.52,0:15:33.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Mom, where is Mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.16,0:15:36.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Found her.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.77,0:15:39.33,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Hey, why did you run to another platform?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.90,0:15:41.26,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}This is too dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.33,0:15:46.15,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Damn Mom! Behind you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.62,0:15:48.25,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}Dang it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.76,0:15:51.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is this? Why is Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.36,0:15:54.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't he say that he would protect me?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.59,0:15:59.71,Radio,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The train will be coming to Platform 7 shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.89,0:16:06.80,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}The criminal walked towards the young detective's back slowly,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.84,0:16:09.09,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}With his hands covered in blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.88,0:16:11.76,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He pushed the innocent one down,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.90,0:16:15.45,Flashback,,0,0,0,,{\be10}And the platform was full of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.14,0:16:24.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's hasn't ended yet, but let's leave it at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.78,0:16:28.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's meaningless to continue now.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.90,0:16:30.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dear... Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.62,0:16:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,heard it from Inspector Nishimura,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.06,0:16:37.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I confirmed everything, and rushed over here immediately.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.49,0:16:42.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal who killed the owner of the jewelry store...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.50,0:16:44.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then diverted our attention onto the robber Asama...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.02,0:16:47.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That criminal is...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.35,0:16:48.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kaetsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.86,0:16:51.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're the only one who can do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.07,0:16:57.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.41,0:17:00.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal is the man called Asama.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.80,0:17:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was seen killing the jewelry store\Nowner and jumping out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.55,0:17:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Asama seen by the witnesses was you in disguise.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.40,0:17:14.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, he's a fleeing criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.10,0:17:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's easy to pretend to be someone whose face is covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.88,0:17:22.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That, the incident of fleeing out of the train...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.07,0:17:24.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How can you explain that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.80,0:17:26.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was inside the train the entire time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.40,0:17:30.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's just a part of your trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.05,0:17:34.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You used the fishing equipment over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.37,0:17:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You killed Asama in his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.59,0:17:43.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the back of his trousers, you hooked a fishing line.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.45,0:17:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then left it outside of the broken window.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.16,0:17:49.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You brought the ends into your room...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.71,0:17:52.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tied one side to something outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.05,0:17:55.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the other end at the door knob.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.71,0:17:56.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then everything is all set.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.64,0:18:00.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you went to the lobby car and shot the owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.08,0:18:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran to Asama's room and shot at the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.78,0:18:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then shot at Detective Mouri and the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.12,0:18:11.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While they weren't paying much attention, you ran up the stairs,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.08,0:18:14.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And cut off one end of the fishing line.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.69,0:18:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then Asama's body would fall out of the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.64,0:18:21.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the time when the criminal ran away,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.25,0:18:24.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the time Asama fell out of the train would be the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.48,0:18:29.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, it created an illusion that the criminal is Asama.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.64,0:18:35.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when Detective Mouri rushed to\Nthe room, he saw the door close.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.38,0:18:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. I forgot to say this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.50,0:18:42.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't there a hook on the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.31,0:18:47.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stuck another fishing line with plastic\Ntape at the back of the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.90,0:18:49.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And taped it at the hook.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.78,0:18:51.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You tied it up with the fishing line on the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.17,0:18:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the line was cut off, this line would\Nbe pulled off at the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.13,0:18:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Due to the weight of the body, the tape will release.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.21,0:19:02.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door would be closed automatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.07,0:19:08.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The evidence is shown on the body's trousers\Non which there is a piece of tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.69,0:19:12.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But... this thing could have been done by someone else too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.51,0:19:18.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, your luggage seems to have\Nthe clothes of the original suspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.02,0:19:21.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ahh, also the sunglasses and the hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.58,0:19:22.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.25,0:19:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Boy...!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.81,0:19:26.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Kaetsu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.10,0:19:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The weak point of this method is the impossibility\Nto throw away the clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.99,0:19:34.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If your luggage is checked,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.72,0:19:37.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There is no way for you to walk away from the crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.19,0:19:42.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To follow the storyline of the novel...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.00,0:19:44.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was just too outrageous.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.35,0:19:48.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is the unpublished work by my favorite author,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.79,0:19:50.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, I believed it would work out perfectly.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.35,0:19:53.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is just what I think, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.84,0:19:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your intention was revenge for the dead\Nwoman from the group of robbers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.36,0:20:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.71,0:20:06.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The target is Izumo Owner who is the drug dealer,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.41,0:20:09.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also the person who allowed her to get addicted to drugs,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.70,0:20:11.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The robbers' head, Asama Yasuji.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.72,0:20:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the novel you took, it unintentionally\Nwas so similar to your own story.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.98,0:20:22.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you decided to follow the novel and start the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.77,0:20:24.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.12,0:20:27.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I forgot to introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.95,0:20:32.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am Kudo Yusaku, the author of the unpublished novel.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.51,0:20:35.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.78,0:20:36.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.80,0:20:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you understand my novel, I hope you\Nwill give yourself up to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.88,0:20:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the ending of the novel is about the criminal\Nwho regretted what he did at the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.89,0:20:52.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And gave himself up to the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.01,0:20:54.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.54,0:22:30.89,Character Card,,0,0,0,,New Millennium Airport
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.47,0:22:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.77,0:22:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did you come to send us off?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.96,0:22:36.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, have something to tell Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.40,0:22:40.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I solved all of Dad's tricks.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.51,0:22:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, it was solved by my own son.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.42,0:22:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sign of "the world's number one\Nmystery novelist" was taken down.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.28,0:22:52.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry. It was fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.57,0:22:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a trap for the buyers.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.65,0:22:58.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because only the first half of the draft was finished, but I\Nthink the criminal thought it was complete and used it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.03,0:23:03.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I recall there was a trick to get rid of the criminal's disguise as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.14,0:23:05.70,Thoughts,,0,0,0,,{\be10}He better not be just making this up.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.70,0:23:12.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a true destiny that at my most critical\Nmoment, you suddenly appeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.74,0:23:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suddenly?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.31,0:23:17.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I remember was beside you at least for two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.06,0:23:19.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.94,0:23:21.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until the moment before I was pushed down,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.92,0:23:23.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You were just standing right there, watching me?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.85,0:23:27.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes I wanted to know whether or not he was the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.07,0:23:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after all, the trick happened in Seikan tunnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.76,0:23:35.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I remained silent to view it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.59,0:23:40.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.21,0:23:43.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, because this is Hokkaido.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.94,0:24:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.56,0:24:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Metropolitan Police Officer Love Story: Part One!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.08,0:24:18.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.72,0:24:19.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exercise bike
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.75,0:24:21.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And next:
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.58,0:24:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone we know will appear as a policeman!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.33,0:24:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.92,0:24:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surprise!
